node.text: recently i’ve been struggling with inspiration in my life and finding meaning inside of my art. i was contacted by @the0nlyariana from her seeing my art here and i felt in my soul that her story was special, so we met. ariana is a strong and beautiful woman who was born into this world in a unique way that many won't experience. ariana educated me on her experience, and that is living with Epidermolysis Bullosa. i don’t want to speak too much for ariana, i think if you go on her page you’ll be able to follow her incredible journey for yourself and see the strength and inspiration that i see in her. i wanted to create a set of portraits showing the seriousness of EB but also the bright light and strength ariana beholds. please take a moment to visit @wefighteb https://www.debra.org to educate yourself further and see how you can be part of helping those in need. EB has no cure and very little funding for care and further research. i believe that it is our responsibility and purpose to stand side by side with another human being who does everything in their life to bring positivity and change. i am extremely honored to be part of that with my art. let’s get this message out, and many more messages.
@ross_lynch

photographing people for me is an incredibly intimate moment where my passion enables me to capture a connection, a tiny piece of magic and in a way my own fantasy, which is reality for me because i invented it. i truly believe that i was born to create because no other feeling i experience compares to being behind a camera. it brings me so much joy, confidence and comfortability. i want to try and pass that feeling on and share my experiences with people, i don’t want to feel disconnected from the world or different to anybody else. i’m not trying to live forever but i’d like to create something that will. so i thank you all for your belief in me and my art and i thank @armanibeauty for allowing me to create for you. let me ask you a question, what makes you feel strong?

i find people so complex and interesting. full of layers and hidden identities. i always question if i’ve ever truly knew anybody else because honestly i’ve never truly knew myself to the full extent. not yet anyway. i’d like us to embrace all the sides to our personality much more. @zoeydeutch and i explored ours together.

Growing up in a small town with not much money in my world, having to go to the local library to use the internet and find whatever way I can to escape, find others who are just like me, feel the way that I do, see life the way that I do. I guess all of those moments, that young person who really had no idea what he was doing, has prepared and led me to moments like this.. a moment that I can finally share with you my darling. @armanibeauty treated me for an entire week in Berlin, to photograph their twenty twenty fragrance campaign ?! Sorry wait, fragrance campaign? How am I even writing this right now?! I can sit here and say that I’m so blessed and lucky to have this opportunity, and partly I am. But I’m also proud of myself, because it hasn’t been easy, it’s been really hard actually. I’ve struggled with myself. I’ve fought for my art time and time again which truly has been a blessing because through all of that pain I developed the strength to fight for your art too, but it hasn’t been easy, and maybe it will never be easy and maybe that’s what makes it even more great. I guess the meaning of my little caption is to ensure you feel the phrase, if I can do it then so can you. Sit with that for a moment. What on earth is stopping you from being great?! Thank you for sharing this moment with me. Here is a moment I shared with wonderful @nicholashoult and @opheliamillaiss , you’ll see more very soon. #armanibeauty side note, thank you Emporio Armani for letting me not over retouch my images. It’s good for people to see what people truly look like. Skin is beautiful. Who wants to look like somebody nobody looks like? Not me.

Honestly the only thing that keeps me happy in this world is creativity. Surrounded by so much bullshit but at least nobody can take this away from me. @eljuanpazurita I dragged you around my studio baby and you let yourself go. You were free.

2008, i’m sixteen years of age, trapped, unaware of what is ahead of me, confused, desperate for a life i do not have, i’m poor, i have nobody to talk too, nobody understands me, nobody feels how i feel, who am i? 2010, i’m becoming ‘somebody’, but who is this person? is it me? is it who i think i should be? i’m making little money, i’m falling in love! 2015, i don’t know 2008 anymore, i’ve changed, i’ve been hurt, i drink a lot now, i’ve seen the world (from a car window!) 2019, i pretend i’m happy. i am happy. i’m sad. fuck, how do i feel? who cares, i’m here and i’m going to create and i’m going to scream to the world that i fucking exist. to be continued... introducing @lilhuddy 🖤

It was a pleasure to portray the talents behind a tv show that dives into a scary subject that so many people feel afraid to talk about. I try my best to talk openly about my struggles in the hopes that it will help somebody else. I often spotlight my inner pain but here I wanted to bring happiness, strength and pride to the fact that we are finally talking to one another and talking loudly. Thank you @netflix for the constant support. Tag a ❤️ if you feel proud! I’m proud of you!

Introducing @notnoen who I quickly became inspired by online after seeing his freedom in expressing himself and defining his own unique style. It reminds me of when I was sixteen, sat in my bedroom cutting up clothes trying to create outfits that defined me so I could express to the world exactly who I was through whichever creative way that I could.

Do you ever feel like the world is caving in on you? Emotions skyrocket so high and plummet so low as if you are trapped in the waves of an unforgiving ocean of thoughts. I do. I don’t feel people say that to themselves enough, or out loud, or at all. When did we become ashamed to feel? Are we considered crazy if we feel? Are we unwell if we feel? Our feelings connect us, help us understand that we are all alive, together, doing the best that we can. I guess I just want to say that I’m proud of you for standing up each morning and letting the world know that you are here, you are just as special as anybody else in this world, you are alive and you have the absolute right to feel and scream it out loud. @matthew_noszka portrays my feelings towards this perfectly.
Some of my favorite and memorable talents that I’ve created with but I never shared.
A visual interpretation of my love life. First comes bliss then comes the massacre.

I met @pom.klementieff one late night at the Chateau Marmont, we locked eyes, started a conversation and instantly connected, more than usual, it felt real, it wasn’t false, we shared our story and from that moment forward I knew I wanted to photograph her and capture who she is, her story, her energy. Thank you Pom for being you. I hope you enjoy these pictures as much as I did creating them. Tag below who I should photograph next and if it’s you, tag yourself because I’m going on tour and I want to create with YOU!

What does photography mean to you? We live in a generation where most people enjoy capturing pictures, creating with their friends, sharing their content. For me it’s a release of my inner thoughts, a direct connection from my mind piercing through my soul entering my fingertips then exploding into a series of still pictures portrayed by another under control of my eye. @nicholasgalitzine and I played with knives yesterday.

Life catapulted another obstacle my way recently, another blessing in disguise, many disguises actually. Photography, art and creativity once again has been my savior, my therapy and my safe space that shot that strength straight back into my soul and reminded me who I am, what is important and where my focus needs to be. Here we have @dylangeick who rides a motorcycle, creates poetry and had never wore leather trousers before meeting me.

Have you ever been in love? So deep in love that it strips you from every aspect of control and being that you are? As an artist this happens to me at least once a week, every photo session I spiral through emotions as if I’m floating within the ocean and silently drowning. Love from the outside seems to last for a minute but it feels like a lifetime in the moment.. I think love is a moment in time, a moment we so easily create in our mind to end before it has even begun. Why can’t we enjoy it when it’s there? Maybe because I, we, are incable of accepting something beautiful because we don’t know how to handle it. I’ve fallen in love twice now and I’m in my mid twenties, both have taught me so much, more than any other lesson in life. I made so many mistakes, I wish I could turn back time but nothing would change because that love is building my strength, I can only be who I am now in this moment and that’s not always a secure healthy person. I dream of love but I fail when I try to validate that love through another being. The key is falling in love with myself, imagine that self empowerment as a human. I will get there. WE WILL GET THERE! Do you agree? Have you been in love?
@brentrivera is my devil in disguise. Don’t be fooled by the outside that we present, we all have demons.

A collection of my moods. Sorry I’ve been distant lately. I’ve been working on creating projects which required me to step back for a moment and open my eyes to my surroundings and my own emotions. The adventure has been challenging but I can’t wait for you to get to know me a little more. How are you? What’s going on with you? Wishing you happiness and creativity, as always.

PS - Your support and warmth that I feel from your love and your messages is a huge part of what gives me the strength to push myself forward and express myself truly. I owe you all a lot of gratitude for being my online family. I am working on projects that include you, scribble below if this is something you’d like to be part of.
Resurrecting my fashion career with heartthrob brothers @dylanjaggerlee & @brandonthomaslee for @interviewmag

Found these hiding in my camera roll and thought they deserved to have their moment.. I also wanted to take this moment to ask how you are? Because I’m not sure we ask each other that question with sincerity enough.
One year later.

I will never tire of the feeling of power and inspiration surging through me when I embrace my camera knowing that the next moments in time will be entirely mine to capture and immortalize exactly as I please. Exposing true connection, freedom and pure honest love. Love for what I get to do every day, every minute and every second of my life. It’s scary because the world plays sort of tricks on you sometimes where you almost believe that your self love and self belief in your own art has to come from others validations or acceptance of your art, your truth, your happiness and your pain. This affected me for so many years but truly I believe to be an artist is to be human and to be human is to feel, wether good or bad and from those feelings should come reflection and creation. We all have a story to be told. A story another can connect with. I connected with so many of you and that opened a brand new side to my art and purpose. I dream to be able to help as many as I can self believe in their art, be proud of their stories, share their vulnerability, embrace their pain, treasure their happiness and scream it all out loud to the world to let everybody know, none of us are alone. I invite you to listen to The Chain by Fleetwood Mac and share your feelings towards these photos of the wonderful and inspiring @_haatepah_ below..

When I create my pictures it’s to remember all of it. To remember the smells, the energy, the feeling, the adrenaline, the happiness, the pain. Otherwise, I don’t understand the point. I have so many questions inside my mind and I’m constantly overthinking everything but never letting it out or well not knowing how too unless through my art. My art being the pure essence of who I am and what I feel, from my own perspective. Honesty, I guess, the best way I know how to be. My emotions slam me into so many walls, sometimes I break the wall down, sometimes I don’t. Sharing this with you, my art, is like a direct pathway to my heart, a clear journey right through my soul, to see who i truly am, in all my elements, good and bad. Isn’t that what art is? A reflection of a time, a being, an emotion, a truth, sometimes a lie.
